			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 44 bard seaks help....<a name="30276"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 24 04 3:30 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>If you're 44 and haven't tried these I'd suggest practicing on low blue mobs until you get the hang of it. I've found solo exp to be much better than group exp so far, but I'm only level 41.
<br />

<br />
Chant kiting = twisting your chants on a mob. I get my third chant in 1 level and I can't wait to see how much damage I do. I already do 96 damage every tick with just 2 chants. This method is the slowest but it's pretty easy.
<br />

<br />
You should have two AE songs: Chords of Dissonance (CoD) and Denon's Disruptive Discord (DDD). If you're dying swarming, this strategy is sure to kill you unless you practice on weak mobs first. Grab a ton of non-casting mobs with the same movement speed and similar HPs, run them around into a ball, then twist your AE dots. When your dot is about to land, you have to cut close enough to the pack to get it to hit the mobs, but not too close or you'll get smacked. There isn't a whole lot of room for error, and if you get stunned... Loading Please Wait.
<br />

<br />
Swarming is my favorite so far. I really can't tell you how to do it better than the guides, but maybe a more experienced bard can. If the mobs are coming after you and not your pet you don't have social mobs, have hard aggro, or didn't have the mobs in a tight enough ball when you had your pet attack. Either way, just keep selo up and you shouldn't die.
<br />
</span></td>
