				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 44 bard seaks help....<a name="30292"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Mar 24 04 4:14 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Pemene:
<br />

<br />
When swarming you have a lot of mobs.  Lets say you have a small swarm of 4 mobs (Frost Giants in GD for example).  You round them up in a tight group and charm one and send it against another.  
<br />

<br />
Most of the giants (should be all but not always) will jump on your pet.  You break the charm at 10-20% with invis(I would say 20% to start) and then twist dots on that low health mob until he dies.  Low health mobs will NOT run if close enough to a social mob, so you usually only worry about runners when you are down to 1 or 2 mobs.
<br />

<br />
Then, target another giant, charm it and send it in.  Same strategy.  You will learn how to toggle targets, how to place the pet and swarm away from bodies so you can loot, etc.  
<br />

<br />
There are great guides going into this with more detail, but that should answer your question.
<br />

<br />
Badji
<br />
Minstril on ARO</span></td>
