			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: 44 bard seaks help....<a name="32802"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Apr 4 04 6:45 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Ok reading these I know what everyone is talking about but you may confuse somebody else. You are all talking about three different types of kiting (there are a few more will explain below) and if someone doesn't pay close attention they may think your all talking about one type of kiting. Ok here it is in a nutshell
<br />
(Be advised I have some gear that is a must. Instruments. and such.
<br />
<b>CHANT KITING</b>
<br />
Grab a mob with any number of DoT's you have. I use:
<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=3567&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=66"> Tuyen's Chant of Disease</a>
<br />
<a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=743&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=59">Tuyen's Chant of Flame</a>
<br />
and <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=707&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=50">Fufil's Curtailing Chant</a>
<br />
SIDE NOTE: 
<br />
I have  <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/eq/items/item.aspx?item=1740">Traveler's Boots</a>. They work great to keep you just a head of mobs while running in circles. And there is no need to twist in Selos there about 5k and I saved up everything and then added profits from baking to purchase. I was level 30 at the time.
<br />

<br />
Now just run around in circles and twist your chants to kill them. I like grabbing an add ever once in a while so I never have just 1 as most mobs will run when down to aprox. 20%. 
<br />
Keep it up till your hands fall off.
<br />

<br />
<b>FEAR KITING</b>
<br />
Grab a mob. Equip your badest weapons and twist  <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=706&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=45">Angstlich's Appalling Screech</a>  (fear) and <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=738&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=42">Selo's Consonant Chain
<br />
</a>. 
<br />
Basically you grab with Chain, Cast fear, It runs you beat on it from behind. Twisting the two. Sometimes adding in <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=707&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=50">Fufil's Curtailing Chant</a> for the MR and maybe <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=702&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=65">McVaxius' Berserker Crescendo</a>  for the attack speed, strength and armor 
<br />

<br />
<b>CHARM KITING</b>
<br />
Agro one mob any way you want. Run by a social mob of the same type. He should agro on you as well. Charm the first one you agroed and sic it on the second mob. 
<br />

<br />
This works with two or more mobs.
<br />

<br />
With <b>2</b> mobs they both beat each other down. You can assist wit DoT's or practice AoE's but if you try to melee the uncharmed mob will go for you. By the time your charm runs out they both should be down to about a bubble (may have to charm twice) kite them the rest of the way down with DoT's
<br />

<br />
Now if you have more than two mobs it’s called:
<br />

<br />
<b>SWARMING</b>. Gather up <b>4</b> or <b>5</b> mobs. (Start out slow. Add more as you become proficient.) Make sure there all social. (Meaning same type or same faction and that they help each other out) Run in circles to gather them into a small group. Charm your chosen pet and sic it on one of the others. They all should attack your pet. (If not just keep kiting them and drawing occasionally close to the fighting group they should attack.) Now make sure you keep an eye on your pet’s health. 
<br />
You can retarget your pet a number of ways. 
<br />
<b>-</b>Manually by trying to pick him out of the crowd. 
<br />
<b>-</b>By clicking on pet health bar in pet window (what I use)
<br />
<b>-</b>Tab buffer (works well if you set it up and charm breaks early)
<br />
<b>-</b>Or pressing F1 twice.
<br />

<br />
<b>GOON SQUAD KITING</b> (stole the name from another post but it is appropriate)
<br />
Grab a few of one type of mob this is your goon squad. Make sure there social and heavy hitters. (NEVER TOUCH THEM. just get Agro by running by) now charm a different mob and send it to its death by making it attack the squad. Break charm with Hide. (Ineffective due to high failure rate) or invisibility.  Then Dot to death. Rinse and repeat. If your able to grab light weights with the non-manna using Solon’s Song of the Sirens Then you can do this non-stop. Occasionally having to pick up a new goon. Just keep an eye on the goons as you may need to DoT one down to get XP for it when it gets low.
<br />

<br />

<br />

<br />
<b>AoE KITING</b>
<br />
Grab a group of social mobs kite, them into a small circle, then hit your AoE’s<a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=703&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=16">Chords of Dissonance</a> and <a target="_new" href="http://www.eqdiva.com/EQ/Song.aspx?s=730&amp;c=1&amp;ForumID=36">Denon's Disruptive Discord
<br />
</a> At 48 you will get another. 
<br />
Anyways you cast the song then at about half way through you need to cut in close to the mobs. This takes timing and it’s something I am not good at. But if you do it right your song hits and the mobs don’t hit you. The benefit of this is you damage all the mobs at once so they all drop around the same time. Mad XP follows.
<br />

<br />
<b>TIPS</b>
<br />
<b>-</b>Always have Selos up. (SoW, Potion ect.)
<br />
<b>-</b>DON&quot;T do in heavely populated zones. As people will run thru your pattern and agro all your mobs. They will die and blame you and everyone will end up Hating you the bard. Because you can kite not because the idiot ran thru your kite pattern.(I never do more than chant kite in a populated zone.)
<br />
<b>-</b>I usually work near zone out incase of emergancy. (but watch for idiots zoning in. I am constantly hitting /who)
<br />
<b>-</b>Make a hot key and spam zone with message. SAMPLE I am curently kiting a number of mobs. if you run thru my pattern you WILL agro the mobs and they will KILL you.
<br />
<b>-</b> If in a heavy faction zone like GD people will &quot;Faction hit&quot; your mobs. You must do at least a DoT on every mob before they die to get all XP just incase some one shot an arrow or something at the mob.
<br />
<b>-</b>I know alot of these tips countermand each other but However there will be times when your in a zone and there are people just traveling thru or working on a quest. 
<br />
<b>-</b>If someone stops to watch what your doing have them join group. Don't Show Off just show them what a bard can do and let them injoy some easy XP. Istead of being mad cause your Soloing those 5 giants and he can barly kill one with out any buffs. He will be happy. He got to practice his archery. or whatever. 
<br />
<b>-</b>If the zone does start getting crowded MOVE ON. 
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
